  <chunk id="30e8d03a5cf6907154b5a3d7c7b23cdc96cf1952.c0" text="Aspergillus PCR in Bronchoalveolar Lavage Fluid for the Diagnosis and Prognosis of Aspergillosis in Patients With Hematological and Non-hematological Conditions">
    <entity charOffset="83-96" id="30e8d03a5cf6907154b5a3d7c7b23cdc96cf1952.c0.e0" ontology_id="DOID_13564" text="Aspergillosis" type="disease"/>
  </chunk>
  <chunk id="30e8d03a5cf6907154b5a3d7c7b23cdc96cf1952.c1" text="Objectives: We evaluated the usefulness of an Aspergillus fumigatus quantitative PCR assay performed in bronchoalveolar lavage fluid (BAL) for the diagnosis and prognosis of both invasive and non-invasive aspergillosis.">
    <entity charOffset="134-137" id="30e8d03a5cf6907154b5a3d7c7b23cdc96cf1952.c1.e0" ontology_id="CHEBI_64198" text="BAL" type="chemical"/>
  </chunk>
  <chunk id="30e8d03a5cf6907154b5a3d7c7b23cdc96cf1952.c2" text="Methods: This 4-year retrospective study involved 613 at-risk patients who had either hematological disorders or other immunosuppressive conditions, notably solid organ transplants. Thirty-five patients had proven/probable aspergillosis and thirteen had chronic non-invasive aspergillosis. We compared PCR, galactomannan index and mycological analysis of BAL.">
    <entity charOffset="223-236" id="30e8d03a5cf6907154b5a3d7c7b23cdc96cf1952.c2.e0" ontology_id="DOID_13564" text="aspergillosis" type="disease"/>
